---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Frequently Asked Questions · AroraMSP"
  description="Common questions about working with AroraMSP. Fixed-fee pricing, data access, remote delivery, and what to expect from a Microsoft 365 consulting engagement."
  page="faq"
  canonical="https://aroramsp.com/faq"
  ogTitle="FAQ - AroraMSP"
  ogDescription="Common questions about working with AroraMSP. Fixed-fee pricing, data access, remote delivery, and what to expect from a Microsoft 365 consulting engagement."
>
  <section class="page wrap">
    <div class="page-head">
      <div class="sec-label">FAQ</div>
      <h1>Common questions.</h1>
      <p>Straightforward answers about how engagements work, what access is needed, and what you get at the end.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-controls">
      <button class="btn btn-ghost btn-sm" id="faqExpandAll">Expand all</button>
      <button class="btn btn-ghost btn-sm" id="faqCollapseAll">Collapse all</button>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-list" id="faqList">

      <div class="faq-item reveal reveal-delay-1" aria-expanded="true">
        <div class="faq-head">
          <h3>I am not technical. Can I still work with you?</h3>
          <span class="faq-chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
          Yes. Most of my clients are not IT people. They run a business and need their Microsoft 365 to work properly and securely. I explain everything in plain language, tell you what matters and what does not, and never bury you in jargon. You do not need to understand the technical detail. That is my job.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item reveal reveal-delay-2" aria-expanded="false">
        <div class="faq-head">
          <h3>You are an independent consultant. Why is that better than hiring a large firm?</h3>
          <span class="faq-chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
          With a large firm, the senior expert scopes your project and then a junior staff member often does the actual work. With me, the person you speak with is the person doing the work, every time. You get senior expertise directly, with no layers and no handoffs.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item reveal reveal-delay-3" aria-expanded="false">
        <div class="faq-head">
          <h3>What access do you need to our Microsoft 365 environment, and is our data safe?</h3>
          <span class="faq-chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
          I start with read-only access, which lets me audit your environment without changing anything. Any changes happen only after you approve them in writing. You keep full control of your tenant throughout and can revoke my access at any time. I never move or copy your data outside your own environment.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item reveal reveal-delay-4" aria-expanded="false">
        <div class="faq-head">
          <h3>What happens if something goes wrong during a migration?</h3>
          <span class="faq-chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
          Every migration has a tested rollback plan before work begins. I work in stages so your team stays productive and nothing changes all at once. If an issue appears, we step back to the last known good state. Downtime is the rare exception, not the norm, because the planning happens before any changes are made.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item reveal reveal-delay-5" aria-expanded="false">
        <div class="faq-head">
          <h3>Do you sell or resell Microsoft licenses?</h3>
          <span class="faq-chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
          No. I take no commissions from Microsoft or any vendor. My only income is the fixed fee you agree to upfront. That means my advice is based entirely on what is right for you, including telling you where you are overpaying and how to reduce your costs.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item reveal reveal-delay-6" aria-expanded="false">
        <div class="faq-head">
          <h3>Do you offer ongoing support after the project ends?</h3>
          <span class="faq-chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
          Every project includes full documentation you own and 30 days of post-launch support. After that, your environment is documented so your own team, or any future IT provider, can maintain it without depending on me. I do not offer ongoing retainers or managed services.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item reveal reveal-delay-7" aria-expanded="false">
        <div class="faq-head">
          <h3>How does fixed-fee pricing work if the scope changes?</h3>
          <span class="faq-chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
          You approve the full cost in writing before any work starts. If something material changes during the project, we discuss it and agree on it before any extra work happens. No surprise invoices, ever.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item reveal reveal-delay-8" aria-expanded="false">
        <div class="faq-head">
          <h3>We may be in a different time zone. Is remote delivery a problem?</h3>
          <span class="faq-chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
          No. All work is delivered remotely, which is standard for Microsoft 365 consulting. You get a weekly written status update, a live change log, and scheduled calls that fit your working hours. Most communication is written and async, so progress never waits on a meeting.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item reveal reveal-delay-9" aria-expanded="false">
        <div class="faq-head">
          <h3>Do you work with businesses in our industry?</h3>
          <span class="faq-chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
          Microsoft 365 works the same way whether you run a law firm, a manufacturing business, a charity, or a logistics company. The security, identity, and email principles are consistent across industries. What changes is your specific compliance requirements and workflows, which we cover during the audit.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item reveal reveal-delay-10" aria-expanded="false">
        <div class="faq-head">
          <h3>How do we get started?</h3>
          <span class="faq-chev">›</span>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
          Book a free 30-minute discovery call. I ask where it hurts, you tell me what you have tried, and I give you an honest view of whether I can help and what it would cost. No sales pitch, no obligation. If I am not the right fit, I will say so.
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="faq-cta">
      <p>Have a question not covered here?</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get in touch →</a>
    </div>

  </section>

